abstract: The president has avoided a strong defense of pro-democracy protesters, but Congress has thrown the issue into his lap.
snippet: The president has avoided a strong defense of pro-democracy protesters, but Congress has thrown the issue into his lap.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has spent months delicately sidestepping Hong Kong’s escalating battle between pro-democracy demonstrators and security services enforcing China’s authoritarian government line.

abstract: After two weeks of public testimony, Americans should have a good sense of why an impeachment inquiry was needed.
snippet: After two weeks of public testimony, Americans should have a good sense of why an impeachment inquiry was needed.
lead_paragraph: In his opening statement on Thursday, the last day of the scheduled public hearings in the House’s impeachment inquiry, Devin Nunes, the top Republican on the House Intelligence Committee, expressed his hope that “today’s hearing marks the merciful end of this spectacle in the impeachment committee.”

abstract: Jon Voight, James Patterson and Alison Krauss were among the honorees.
snippet: Jon Voight, James Patterson and Alison Krauss were among the honorees.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In honoring the actor Jon Voight, an outspoken Trump supporter, with the National Medal of the Arts on Thursday, President Trump described him as “somebody I happen to really like.”

abstract: “Triggered,” published Nov. 5, topped the best-seller list thanks in part to a big order from the Republican National Committee.
snippet: “Triggered,” published Nov. 5, topped the best-seller list thanks in part to a big order from the Republican National Committee.
lead_paragraph: When Donald Trump Jr.’s new book “Triggered” appeared at the top of the New York Times best-seller list this month, a debate erupted over how and why it had claimed the No. 1 spot.

abstract: His exorbitant demands on the South alienate yet another ally in a dangerous region.
snippet: His exorbitant demands on the South alienate yet another ally in a dangerous region.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s conviction that allies are getting American military protection at a bargain-basement price is well known. It is also dangerous, as his current tiff with South Korea demonstrates.

abstract: The Navy SEAL insignia is tough to earn and, except when the White House intervenes, easy to lose.
snippet: The Navy SEAL insignia is tough to earn and, except when the White House intervenes, easy to lose.
lead_paragraph: It is a ritual that has been repeated at many funerals of Navy SEALs and dramatized in Hollywood movies: SEALs approach a gravesite one by one, remove the gold-colored pin from the left breast of their dress uniforms and pound them into the coffin of a fallen comrade. The living mourn, with the primary symbol of their brotherhood missing, to be replaced only after the dead have been buried.

abstract: Talks on the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement will continue through the Thanksgiving break, with a vote possible in the weeks ahead, House leaders said.
snippet: Talks on the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement will continue through the Thanksgiving break, with a vote possible in the weeks ahead, House leaders said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic lawmakers left the capital for the Thanksgiving break on Thursday without a final agreement on President Trump’s revised North American trade deal, prolonging a difficult negotiation with the administration on one of the president’s trade priorities.

abstract: A House committee and prosecutors in Manhattan have subpoenaed the records.
snippet: A House committee and prosecutors in Manhattan have subpoenaed the records.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a pair of filings on Thursday, a House committee and Manhattan prosecutors urged the Supreme Court to clear the way for disclosure of President Trump’s financial records.

abstract: Mr. Obama, in his latest remarks about the Democratic primary race, said the party should focus less on differences among the candidates and more on defeating President Trump.
snippet: Mr. Obama, in his latest remarks about the Democratic primary race, said the party should focus less on differences among the candidates and more on defeating President Trump.
lead_paragraph: LOS ALTOS HILLS, Calif. — Former President Barack Obama urged Democrats on Thursday to “chill out” about the party’s 2020 field and to avoid putting candidates through “purity tests,” and warned that average voters were “nervous about changes that might take away what little they have.”
